<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control(Japan)/10–2545:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-25T18:00:00+03:00">October 25, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 25—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>3659. [For Secretary No. 1.] Had 3-hour frank friendly talk alone
                                    with Stalin.</p>
                                <p>He stated control Japan is first question requiring settlement.
                                    Any new information on our policy would be helpful.</p>
                                <pb facs="0798" n="786" xml:id="pg_786"/>
                                <p>Re procedure at London it is now clear Molotov was acting
                                    entirely under instructions. Made some progress though still
                                    inconclusive. Meeting again tomorrow.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>